4 HR____ MOURNING THE DEATH OF WALTER E. TURNER.
5
6 WHEREAS, it is with deep sorrow and regret that we
7 note the lamentable death of Walter E. Turner of Citronelle,
8 Alabama, on February 16, 2026, at the age of 77 years; and
9 WHEREAS, born February 6, 1949, Walter Turner was a
10 graduate of Citronelle High School, Class of 1967, and
11 continued his education at Auburn University, where he
12 earned a Bachelor's Degree in Horticulture; and
13 WHEREAS, he devoted many years of service to his
14 profession, including three decades at Searcy Hospital and
15 an additional 10 years working for the City of Citronelle,
16 where his dedication and expertise contributed to the
17 betterment of his community; and
18 WHEREAS, Mr. Turner's faith was central to his life,
19 and after being ordained as a deacon in 1983, he faithfully
20 served in various church congregations, including Bethel
21 Baptist Church, Living Word Church, Memorial Baptist Church,
22 and First Baptist Church, offering his time, leadership, and
23 encouragement to those around him; and
24 WHEREAS, he enjoyed a wide range of pursuits that
25 reflected both his love of nature and his appreciation for
26 simple fellowship, including gardening, hunting, fishing,
27 cooking, and spending time with family and friends at his
28 cabin and on his front porch; and
Page 1

cabin and on his front porch; and
HR175 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, he also shared a close bond with his
30 brother, with whom he spent many hours woodworking, creating
31 not only handcrafted pieces but also lasting memories; he
32 was widely known for his warmth, humor, and welcoming
33 spirit, qualities that enabled him to form lasting
34 friendships and to make others feel valued and at ease in
35 his presence; and
36 WHEREAS, he is preceded by his father, Ervin Turner;
37 mother, Johnnie Bell Lankford; and brother, David Lloyd
38 Turner; and
39 WHEREAS, left to cherish his memory are his loving
40 wife of 55 years, Carol Turner; children, Corey Raybon
41 (Matt) and Walt Turner (Sandi); grandchildren, Hope Griffin
42 (Nick), Raegan Reynolds, Brady Turner, Blake Turner (Lexie),
43 and Gabe Reynolds; great-granddaughters, Addison and
44 Charlotte; brother, Rickey Turner (Carolyn); sister, Karen
45 Hobbs (Marc); and his legacy lives on in the hearts of his
46 multitude of nieces, nephews, cousins, other relatives, and
47 countless friends who were touched by his kindness and
48 spirit; and
49 WHEREAS, Mr. Turner was a valued member of the
50 community and loved by many; we join with others to
51 celebrate his life and to mourn his death; although his
52 presence will be greatly missed, his memory will be
53 cherished in the hearts and minds of those who were
54 fortunate to know him; now therefore,
55 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
56 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That the death of Walter E. Turner
Page 2

LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That the death of Walter E. Turner
